  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Localize Date Formatting on Polish Homepage News Section\n\nEnsure all date displays in the news section of the Polish homepage are formatted in Polish language and locale conventions.\n\nRequirements:\n- Identify all date elements currently displaying in English within the Polish homepage news section\n- Update date formatting to use Polish locale (pl-PL)\n- Apply Polish month names, day names, and date format conventions\n- Verify date formatting respects Polish grammar rules (e.g., genitive case for months)\n- Check for any other text elements in the news section that may be in incorrect language\n- Ensure timezone handling remains correct after locale changes\n- Test with various date scenarios (today, past dates, future dates, different months)\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Relative dates (e.g., \"2 days ago\" should display as \"2 dni temu\")\n- Date ranges spanning multiple months or years\n- Abbreviated vs. full date formats\n- Any dynamically generated date strings from APIs or backend services\n\nDependencies:\n- Confirm the locale/internationalization library being used in the project\n- Verify Polish translation files include all necessary date-related strings\n- Check if other language versions have similar issues requiring fixes",
